from durtralp ralph durtschi subject re iisi clock upgrade hi i have be get a lot of request for thi information so i think i would post it for those interest party sorry for length to increase the maciisi speed to or the clock must be change from to or respectively thi be do by go to a static-free work station or put some aluminum foil down to work on open up the si by lift the tab at the back of the case remove the hard disk by disconnect the power and scsi cable spread the tab and lift the drive out remove the flopy drive remove the power supply by spread the tab in front and lift the supply straight up and out remove the fan by press the ear together at the back bottom side of the fan and lift straight up and out remove the mother board by spread the tab on the leave and right side of the board and slide the board forward then lift the board out all connector on the back of the board must be remove first desolder the clock the one closest to the memory module thi be not easy even for a skilled solderer get an ic socket with the round pin and remove fmy of the pin by push them up from the bottom with long nose plier put the fmy pin in the hole vacate by the clock and solder them in a or clock large power transistor heat sink on the processor chip and the other large chip just to the right of the processor and figure some way to hold the heat sync in place i make a simple clamp by put a fmy inch screw up through the hole in the board between the two chip mount the screw use insulate washer screw a cro member down over the heat sync to hold them in place do use too much pressure put it all back together and go-for-it disclaimer thi be only the procedure i use and be not authorize by anyone you be on ymy own for thi procedure i quite sure it will void ymy warentee bye for now ralph durtschi idaho state university email durtralp 